info.name: Apache Detection
author: philippedelteil
info.description: Some Apache servers have the version on the response header. The OpenSSL version can be also obtained

curl-command: curl -X 'GET' -d '' -H 'Accept: */*' -H 'Accept-Language: en' -H 'User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.3; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/41.0.2226.0 Safari/537.36' 'http://luispozo.etsisi.upm.es'

info.name: Monitorix
author: geeknik
info.description: Monitorix is a free, open source, lightweight system monitoring tool designed to monitor as many services and system resources as possible.

curl-command: curl -X 'GET' -d '' -H 'Accept: */*' -H 'Accept-Language: en' -H 'User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux x86_64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/41.0.2227.0 Safari/537.36' 'http://luispozo.etsisi.upm.es/monitorix-cgi/monitorix.cgi?mode=localhost&graph=all&when=1day'

info.name: OpenSSH Username Enumeration <= v7.7
author: r3dg33k
daffainfo
forgedhallpass
info.description: OpenSSH through 7.7 is prone to a user enumeration vulnerability due to not delaying bailout for an invalid authenticating user until after the packet containing the request has been fully parsed, related to auth2-gss.c, auth2-hostbased.c, and auth2-pubkey.c.

info.name: OpenSSH username enumeration < v7.3
author: iamthefrogy
forgedhallpass
info.description: OpenSSH before 7.3 is vulnerable to username enumeration and DoS vulnerabilities.

curl-command: curl -X 'GET' -d '' -H 'Accept: */*' -H 'Accept-Language: en' -H 'Forwarded: 127.0.0.1' -H 'User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/89.0.4389.114 Safari/537.36' -H 'X-Client-IP: 127.0.0.1' -H 'X-Forwarded-By: 127.0.0.1' -H 'X-Forwarded-For: 127.0.0.1' -H 'X-Forwarded-For-IP: 127.0.0.1' -H 'X-Forwarded-Host: 127.0.0.1' -H 'X-Host: 127.0.0.1' -H 'X-Originating-IP: 127.0.0.1' -H 'X-Remote-Addr: 127.0.0.1' -H 'X-Remote-IP: 127.0.0.1' -H 'X-True-IP: 127.0.0.1' 'http://luispozo.etsisi.upm.es/server-status'
